Display vBulletin forum latest threads on HTML pages
via external.php javascript output via javascript.

Copyright 2005 - Computer Help Forum - www.cpurigs.com
noppid @lakecs.com

This code will display a forum's recent posts on any HTML page.
The table colors are CSS controlled.
The width is controlled by wrapping the code in a simple table
with the width set as needed. You must enable the javascript
output of your forum's external.php.

1)	Edit the below CSS as necessary...

<style type="text/css">
<!--
.headtd
{
	background-color: #CCCCCC;
	color: #000000;
}
.headtd a:link
{
	background-color: #CCCCCC;
	color: #990000;
}
.headtd a:visited
{
	background-color: #CCCCCC;
	color: #990000;
}
.headtd a:hover
{
	background-color: #CCCCCC;
	color: #666666;
}
.headtd a:active
{
	background-color: #CCCCCC;
	color: #666666;
}

.linktd
{
	background-color: #F5F5F5;
	color: #000000;
}
.linktd a:link
{
	background-color: #F5F5F5;
	color: #990000;
}
.linktd a:visited
{
	background-color: #F5F5F5;
	color: #990000;
}
.linktd a:hover
{
	background-color: #F5F5F5;
	color: #666666;
}
.linktd a:active
{
	background-color: #F5F5F5;
	color: #666666;
}
//-->
</style>

2)	On your HTML page, locate </head> and place the
	CSS code above the </head> tag.

3)	Place this code on the HTML page where you want
	the recent threads to display. Change the URL to
	point to your forum's external.php.

<script type="text/javascript" src="http://www.riderinfo.com/forums/external.php?type=js"></script>

4)	Place this code below that. This controls the width.
	edit the width tag as necessary.

<table><tr><td align="center" width="160">

5)	Place this javascript code below the above table code.
	Edit the  number of links, forum name and forum link
	as necessary.


<script type="text/javascript">
<!--
// Copyright 2005 - Computer Help Forum - www.cpurigs.com
// Do not remove this copyright

// member edits number of links to display.
var num_Of_Links = 15;

// admin enters..

// Forum name.
var forumName = "Motorcycle Forum";

// Forum Link. Include trailing slash.
var forumLink = "http://www.riderinfo.com/forums/";

// Nothing to edit past here unless you know what you are doing.

var threadLink = forumLink + "showthread.php?t=";

document.writeln('<table width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" border="1" align="center">');
document.writeln('<tr><td class="headtd" align="center">');
document.writeln('<a href="' +  forumLink + '" target="new">' + forumName + '<\/a>');
document.writeln("<\/td><\/tr>");
for (i = 0; i < num_Of_Links; i++)
{
	document.writeln('<tr><td class="linktd" align="center">');
	document.writeln('<a href="' + threadLink + threads[i]["threadid"] + '" target="new">' + threads[i]["title"] + '<\/a><br \/>');
	document.writeln('<\/td><\/tr>');
}
document.writeln('<\/table>');
//-->
</script>

6)	Place this code below the above JS to close the sizing table.

</td></tr></table>

Done!
